Package swingtree.style

Interface Layout

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Layout.BorderLayoutInstaller, Layout.ForBoxLayout, Layout.ForFlowLayout, Layout.ForMigLayout, Layout.GridLayoutInstaller, Layout.None, Layout.Unspecific
    public interface Layout
    Implementations of this are layout configuration for a component, which are value objects that can be created through various factory methods like border(), flow(), grid(int, int)... and then supplied to the style API through ComponentStyleDelegate.layout(Layout) so that the layout can then be installed onto a component dynamically.

    The various layout types hold necessary information and implementation logic required for installing the layout of a component through the installFor(JComponent) method, which will be used by the style engine of SwingTree every time the layout object state changes compared to the previous state effectively making the layout mechanics of a component fully dynamic.

    You may implement this interface to create custom layout configurations for other kinds of LayoutManager implementations.
